==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*rūhwa-''.  Cognate with Middle Low German [[ruch|rūch]] (Dutch [[ruig]]), Old High German ''rūh'' (German [[rauh]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ru:x/

===Adjective===
'''rūh'''
# [[rough]], [[hairy]]
#:''Min broðer ys ruh and ic eom smeðe'': my brother is hairy and I am smooth.  (''Genesis'')

